{"title_page": "Mateus Galiano da Costa", "text_new": "{{short description|Angolan footballer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Mateus\n| image = \n| fullname = Mateus Galiano da Costa\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1984|6|19|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Luanda]], Angola\n| height = {{height|m=1.76}}\n| position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n| currentclub = [[Boavista F.C.|Boavista]]\n| clubnumber = 9\n| youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 =\n| years1 = 2001\u20132003 | clubs1 = [[C.D. Beja|Desportivo Beja]] | caps1 = | goals1 =\n| years2 = 2003\u20132004 | clubs2 = [[Sporting CP B|Sporting B]] | caps2 = 23 | goals2 = 9\n| years3 = 2004\u20132005 | clubs3 = [[Casa Pia A.C.|Casa Pia]] | caps3 = 35 | goals3 = 13\n| years4 = 2005 | clubs4 = [[F.C. Lixa|Lixa]] | caps4 = 10 | goals4 = 3\n| years5 = 2006\u20132007 | clubs5 = [[Gil Vicente F.C.|Gil Vicente]] | caps5 = 16 | goals5 = 7\n| years6 = 2007\u20132008 | clubs6 = [[Boavista F.C.|Boavista]] | caps6 = 25 | goals6 = 2\n| years7 = 2008\u20132013 | clubs7 = [[C.D. Nacional|Nacional]] | caps7 = 117 | goals7 = 28\n| years8 = 2014\u20132015 | clubs8 = [[C.D. Primeiro de Agosto|1\u00ba Agosto]] | caps8 = 44 | goals8 = 13\n| years9 = 2016\u20132017 | clubs9 = [[F.C. Arouca|Arouca]] | caps9 = 46 | goals9 = 7\n| years10 = 2017\u2013 | clubs10 = [[Boavista F.C.|Boavista]] | caps10 = 65 | goals10 = 11\n| totalcaps = | totalgoals = \n| nationalyears1 = 2006\u2013 | nationalteam1 = [[Angola national football team|Angola]] | nationalcaps1 = 65 | nationalgoals1 = 12\n| club-update = 30 August 2019\n| nationalteam-update = 6 October 2019\n}}\n\n'''Mateus Galiano da Costa''' (born 19 June 1984), known simply as '''Mateus''', is an Angolan professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for Portuguese club [[Boavista F.C.]] as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]].\n\nHe spent practically all of his career in Portugal, recording over 270 games and 50 goals in the [[Primeira Liga]]. He represented four teams in the division, mainly [[C.D. Nacional|Nacional]] and [[Boavista F.C.|Boavista]].\n\nMateus made his debut for [[Angola national football team|Angola]] in 2006 and earned over 60 caps. He was selected for the [[2006 FIFA World Cup|2006 World Cup]] and four [[Africa Cup of Nations]] tournaments.\n\n==Club career==\nMateus was born in [[Luanda]]. After started playing professionally for modest [[Portugal|Portuguese]] teams (he had a stint with [[Sporting CP]], but never moved past [[Sporting CP B|their reserves]]), he signed in January 2006 with [[Gil Vicente F.C.]] of the [[Primeira Liga]]. He scored in his debut on 5 February, in a 5\u20130 home win against [[Vit\u00f3ria F.C.|Vit\u00f3ria de Set\u00fabal]].<ref>[http://www.record.xl.pt/arquivo/interior.aspx?content_id=260203 Gil Vicente-V. Set\u00fabal, 5\u20130: Grande treino do Gil (Gil Vicente-V. Set\u00fabal, 5\u20130: Great Gil training)]; [[Record (newspaper)|Record]], 6 February 2006 (in Portuguese)</ref>\n\nHowever, Mateus was at the centre of a judicial controversy that erupted in Portuguese football, known as ''Caso Mateus'' (Mateus Affair), after a supposedly illegal registration by the [[Barcelos, Portugal|Barcelos]] club. Following a lengthy judicial battle between Gil and [[C.F. Os Belenenses]], [[2005\u201306 Primeira Liga|the former were relegated]].<ref>[http://www.record.xl.pt/arquivo/interior.aspx?content_id=277046 \"Caso Mateus\": Gil Vicente pede explica\u00e7\u00f5es (\"Mateus Affair\": Gil Vicente ask for explanations)]; Record, 11 July 2006 (in Portuguese)</ref><ref>[http://www.uefa.com/news/newsid=447593.html Belenenses spared the drop]; UEFA, 22 August 2006</ref>\n\nAfter an uneventful [[2006\u201307 Liga de Honra|season]] with Gil Vicente in the [[Segunda Liga|second division]], greatly delayed by the legal consequences,<ref>[http://www.record.xl.pt/arquivo/interior.aspx?content_id=294044 Gil Vicente fica na Liga de Honra (Gil Vicente stay in Honour League)]; Record, 15 January 2007 (in Portuguese)</ref> Mateus joined [[Boavista F.C.]] for the [[2007\u201308 Primeira Liga|2007\u201308 campaign]]. His new team was also eventually relegated, due to irregularities.<ref>[http://www.uefa.com/memberassociations/news/newsid=693942.html Porto docked points, Boavista demoted]; UEFA, 9 May 2008</ref>\n\nIn [[2008\u201309 Primeira Liga|2008\u201309]], Mateus moved to [[Madeira]]'s [[C.D. Nacional]],<ref>[https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/nacional-mateus-assina-por-quatro-anos-com-acordo-do-boavista Nacional: Mateus assina por quatro anos com acordo do Boavista (Nacional: Mateus signs for four years after Boavista agree)]; Mais Futebol, 17 June 2008 (in Portuguese)</ref> being a regular in their attack as they [[2009\u201310 UEFA Europa League|qualified]] for the [[UEFA Europa League]]. In the same season, he played six games and scored four goals as they reached the semi-finals of the [[Ta\u00e7a de Portugal]], including one in each leg of a 5\u20132 aggregate elimination by [[F.C. Pa\u00e7os de Ferreira]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Pa\u00e7os de Ferreira na final da Ta\u00e7a de Portugal |url=https://www.rtp.pt/noticias/futebol-nacional/pacos-de-ferreira-na-final-da-taca-de-portugal_d262989 |accessdate=19 February 2020 |publisher=R\u00e1dio e Televis\u00e3o de Portugal|date=22 April 2009 |language=Portuguese}}</ref>\n\nMateus continued to be play frequently for the better part of the following years, notably netting nine goals in 24 matches in the [[2011\u201312 Primeira Liga|2011\u201312 season]]. On 7 April 2012, he netted twice in a 4\u20132 win at [[Funchal]] rivals [[C.S. Mar\u00edtimo]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Nacional goleia Mar\u00edtimo no d\u00e9rbi madeirense|trans-title=Nacional thrash Mar\u00edtimo in the Madeiran derby |url=https://www.rtp.pt/noticias/1a-liga/nacional-goleia-maritimo-no-derbi-madeirense_d543096 |accessdate=19 February 2020 |publisher=R\u00e1dio e Televis\u00e3o de Portugal |date=7 April 2012 |language=Portuguese}}</ref>\n\nOn 17 November 2013, Mateus moved to his country's league for the first time, signing for [[C.D. Primeiro de Agosto]] for the new year.<ref>{{cite news |title=Avan\u00e7ado do Nacional Mateus vai representar angolanos do 1\u00ba de Agosto|trans-title=Nacional striker Mateus will represent Angolans |url=https://www.rtp.pt/noticias/futebol-nacional/avancado-do-nacional-mateus-vai-representar-angolanos-do-1o-de-agosto_d696478 |accessdate=19 February 2020 |publisher=[[R\u00e1dio e Televis\u00e3o de Portugal]] |date=17 November 2013 |language=Portuguese}}</ref> In December 2015, he agreed a move back to Portugal's top flight, joining [[F.C. Arouca]] for the remainder of the season with the option of one more.<ref>{{cite news |title=Arouca: Mateus \u00e9 refor\u00e7o para o ataque a partir de janeiro|trans-title=Arouca: Mateus is addition for the attack starting from January |url=https://tvi24.iol.pt/liga/mercado/arouca-mateus-e-reforco-para-o-ataque-a-partir-de-janeiro |accessdate=19 February 2020 |publisher=[[TVI 24]] |date=20 December 2015 |language=Portuguese}}</ref>\n\nMateus returned to Boavista on 23 June 2017, signing a one-year deal a decade after first joining the club.<ref>{{cite news |title=Angolano Mateus est\u00e1 de volta ao Boavista |trans-title=Angolan Mateus back at Boavista|url=https://www.ojogo.pt/futebol/1a-liga/boavista/noticias/angolano-mateus-esta-de-volta-ao-boavista-8586083.html |accessdate=19 February 2020 |work=O Jogo |date=23 June 2017 |language=Portuguese}}</ref> After six goals in 31 games in his first season back at the ''[[Est\u00e1dio do Bessa]]'', he extended his link until 2020.<ref>{{cite news |title=Mateus renova com o Boavista at\u00e9 2020 |trans-title=Mateus renews with Boavista until 2020|url=https://desporto.sapo.ao/futebol/primeira-liga/artigos/mateus-renova-com-o-boavista-ate-2020 |accessdate=19 February 2020 |publisher=[[SAPO (company)|SAPO]] |date=16 May 2019 |language=Portuguese}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nAn [[Angola national football team|Angola international]] since 2006, Mateus was called up to [[2006 FIFA World Cup|that year]]'s [[FIFA World Cup]], playing in all three group stage matches including the entire 0\u20131 loss against [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]].<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/world_cup_2006/4852704.stm Angola 0\u20131 Portugal]; [[BBC Sport]], 11 June 2006</ref> He also added three substitute appearances in the [[2008 Africa Cup of Nations]], as the ''Palancas Negras'' reached the quarter-finals.\n\nOn 8 October 2011, Mateus scored as Angola won 2\u20130 away to [[Guinea-Bissau national football team|Guinea-Bissau]] to pip [[Uganda national football team|Uganda]] to a spot at the [[2012 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Magalh\u00e3es |first1=Anaximandro |title=Angola est\u00e1 no Campeonato Africano das Na\u00e7\u00f5es|trans-title=Angola is in the Africa Cup of Nations |url=http://jornaldeangola.sapo.ao/desporto/futebol/angola_esta_no_campeonato_africano_das_nacoes |accessdate=19 February 2020 |work=Jornal de Angola |date=9 October 2011 |language=Portuguese}}</ref> At the tournament in Gabon and Equatorial Guinea, he scored the first goal of their opening 2\u20131 win against [[Burkina Faso national football team|Burkina Faso]], but [[Lito Vidigal]]'s team were eliminated from the group.<ref>{{cite news |title=Angola seal victory over Burkina Faso |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/sport/football/2012/01/201212221342669351.html |accessdate=19 February 2020 |publisher=[[Al Jazeera]] |date=22 January 2012}}</ref> A year later, he started all three games as the team exited at the same stage.\n\nMateus scored four times in [[2019 Africa Cup of Nations qualification|qualification]] for the [[2019 Africa Cup of Nations]], coming in braces in wins over [[Mauritania national football team|Mauritania]] (4\u20131) and Burkina Faso (2\u20131).<ref>{{cite news |title=CAN\u20192019: Angola esmagou a Maurit\u00e2nia|trans-title=ACN'2019: Angola crushed Mauritania |url=http://www.rfi.fr/pt/angola/20181012-can-2019-angola-esmagou-mauritania-futebol-palancas-negras-angolanos |accessdate=19 February 2020 |publisher=RFI |date=12 October 2018 |language=Portuguese}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Angola beats Burkina Faso and rejoins the race for the Cup |url=https://www.plataformamedia.com/en-uk/sport/football/angola-beats-burkina-faso-and-rejoins-the-race-for-the-cup--10196714.html |accessdate=19 February 2020 |date=19 November 2018}}</ref> He [[Captain (association football)|captained]] the side at the finals in Egypt, falling again at the first hurdle.<ref>{{cite news |title=CAN 2019: Mateus, capit\u00e3o dos Palancas Negras abriu o cora\u00e7\u00e3o|trans-title=ACN 2019: Mateus, captain of the ''Palancas Negras'' opened his heart |url=http://www.rfi.fr/pt/angola/20190705-can-2019-mateus-capitao-dos-palancas-negras-abriu-o-coracao-angola-futebol |accessdate=19 February 2020 |publisher=RFI |date=5 July 2019 |language=Portuguese}}</ref>\n\n===International goals===\n{{updated|12 October 2018}} (Angola score listed first, score column indicates score after each Mateus goal)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/mateus-galiano-da-costa/98/matches/|title=Mateus \u2013 Matches|publisher=Soccerway|accessdate=12 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/ango-mateus-intl.html|title=Mateus Galiano da Costa \u2013 International Appearances|publisher=[[Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation|RSSSF]]|accessdate=10 March 2017}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=font-size:95%\n!#\n!Date\n!Venue\n!Opponent\n!Score\n!Result\n!Competition\n|-\n|1.\n|29 April 2006\n|[[Setsoto Stadium]], [[Maseru]], [[Lesotho]]\n|{{fb|Mauritius}}\n|<center>4\u20131</center>\n|<center>5\u20131</center>\n|rowspan=2|[[2006 COSAFA Cup]]\n|-\n|2.\n|30 April 2006\n|Setsoto Stadium, Maseru, Lesotho\n|{{fb|Lesotho|1987}}\n|<center>1\u20130</center>\n|<center>3\u20131</center>\n|-\n|3.\n|8 October 2006\n|[[Est\u00e1dio da Cidadela]], [[Luanda]], [[Angola]]\n|{{fb|Kenya}}\n|<center>2\u20130</center>\n|<center>3\u20131</center>\n|[[2008 Africa Cup of Nations qualification#Qualifying round#Group 6|2008 Africa Cup of Nations qualification]]\n|-\n|4.\n|12 August 2009\n|[[Est\u00e1dio do Restelo]], [[Lisbon]], [[Portugal]]\n|{{fb|Togo}}\n|<center>2\u20130</center>\n|<center>2\u20130</center>\n|[[Exhibition game|Friendly]]\n|-\n|5.\n|8 October 2011\n|[[Est\u00e1dio 24 de Setembro]], [[Bissau]], [[Guinea-Bissau]]\n|{{fb|Guinea-Bissau}}\n|<center>2\u20130</center>\n|<center>2\u20130</center>\n|[[2012 Africa Cup of Nations qualification#Qualifying group stage#Group J|2012 Africa Cup of Nations qualification]]\n|-\n|6.\n|14 January 2012\n|[[Est\u00e1dio Nacional do Chiazi]], [[Cabinda (city)|Cabinda]], Angola\n|{{fb|Sierra Leone}}\n|<center>2\u20131</center>\n|<center>3\u20131</center>\n|Friendly\n|-\n|7.\n|22 January 2012\n|[[Nuevo Estadio de Malabo|Nuevo Estadio]], [[Malabo]], [[Equatorial Guinea]]\n|{{fb|Burkina Faso}}\n|<center>1\u20130</center>\n|<center>2\u20131</center>\n|[[2012 Africa Cup of Nations Group B|2012 Africa Cup of Nations]]\n|-\n|8.\n|17 October 2015\n|[[Rand Stadium]], [[Johannesburg]], [[South Africa]]\n|{{fb|RSA}}\n|<center>1\u20130</center>\n|<center>2\u20130</center>\n|[[2016 African Nations Championship qualification]]\n|-\n|9.\n|rowspan=2|12 October 2018\n|rowspan=2|[[Est\u00e1dio 11 de Novembro]], Luanda, Angola\n|rowspan=2|{{fb|MTN}}\n|<center>1\u20131</center>\n|rowspan=2|<center>4\u20131</center>\n|rowspan=4|[[2019 Africa Cup of Nations qualification Group I|2019 Africa Cup of Nations qualification]]\n|-\n|10.\n|<center>2\u20131</center>\n|-\n|11.\n|rowspan=2|18 November 2018\n|rowspan=2|Est\u00e1dio 11 de Novembro, Luanda, Angola\n|rowspan=2|{{fb|BFA}}\n|<center>1\u20130</center>\n|rowspan=2|<center>2\u20131</center>\n|-\n|12.\n|<center>2\u20130</center>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{ForaDeJogo|name=Mateus}}\n* {{NFT player|id=14354|name=Mateus}}\n* {{Soccerway|mateus-galiano-da-costa/98|Mateus}}\n\n{{Boavista F.C. squad}}\n{{Navboxes colour\n|title=Angola squads\n|bg=#db000d\n|fg=#fbea0e\n|list1=\n{{Angola Squad 2006 World Cup}}\n{{Angola Squad 2008 Africa Cup of Nations}}\n{{Angola Squad 2012 Africa Cup of Nations}}\n{{Angola squad 2013 Africa Cup of Nations}}\n{{Angola squad 2019 Africa Cup of Nations}}\n}}\n{{Ta\u00e7a de Portugal top scorers}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mateus Galiano Da Costa}}\n[[Category:1984 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Luanda]]\n[[Category:Angolan footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Primeira Liga players]]\n[[Category:LigaPro players]]\n[[Category:Portuguese Second Division players]]\n[[Category:Sporting CP B players]]\n[[Category:Casa Pia A.C. players]]\n[[Category:F.C. Lixa players]]\n[[Category:Gil Vicente F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Boavista F.C. players]]\n[[Category:C.D. Nacional players]]\n[[Category:F.C. Arouca players]]\n[[Category:Girabola players]]\n[[Category:C.D. Primeiro de Agosto players]]\n[[Category:Angola international footballers]]\n[[Category:2006 FIFA World Cup players]]\n[[Category:2008 Africa Cup of Nations players]]\n[[Category:2012 Africa Cup of Nations players]]\n[[Category:2013 Africa Cup of Nations players]]\n[[Category:2019 Africa Cup of Nations players]]\n[[Category:Angolan expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Portugal]]\n[[Category:Angolan expatriate sportspeople in Portugal]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Mateus\n| image = \n| fullname = Mateus Galiano da Costa\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1984|6|19|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Luanda]], Angola\n| height = {{height|m=1.76}}\n| position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n| currentclub = [[Boavista F.C.|Boavista]]\n| clubnumber = 9\n| youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 =\n| years1 = 2001\u20132003 | clubs1 = [[C.D. Beja|Desportivo Beja]] | caps1 = | goals1 =\n| years2 = 2003\u20132004 | clubs2 = [[Sporting CP B|Sporting B]] | caps2 = 23 | goals2 = 9\n| years3 = 2004\u20132005 | clubs3 = [[Casa Pia A.C.|Casa Pia]] | caps3 = 35 | goals3 = 13\n| years4 = 2005 | clubs4 = [[F.C. Lixa|Lixa]] | caps4 = 10 | goals4 = 3\n| years5 = 2006\u20132007 | clubs5 = [[Gil Vicente F.C.|Gil Vicente]] | caps5 = 16 | goals5 = 7\n| years6 = 2007\u20132008 | clubs6 = [[Boavista F.C.|Boavista]] | caps6 = 25 | goals6 = 2\n| years7 = 2008\u20132013 | clubs7 = [[C.D. Nacional|Nacional]] | caps7 = 117 | goals7 = 28\n| years8 = 2014\u20132015 | clubs8 = [[C.D. Primeiro de Agosto|1\u00ba Agosto]] | caps8 = 44 | goals8 = 13\n| years9 = 2016\u20132017 | clubs9 = [[F.C. Arouca|Arouca]] | caps9 = 46 | goals9 = 7\n| years10 = 2017\u2013 | clubs10 = [[Boavista F.C.|Boavista]] | caps10 = 65 | goals10 = 11\n| totalcaps = | totalgoals = \n| nationalyears1 = 2006\u2013 | nationalteam1 = [[Angola national football team|Angola]] | nationalcaps1 = 65 | nationalgoals1 = 12\n| club-update = 30 August 2019\n| nationalteam-update = 6 October 2019\n}}\n\n'''Mateus Galiano da Costa''' (born 19 June 1984), known simply as '''Mateus''', is an Angolan professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for Portuguese club [[Boavista F.C.]] as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]].\n\nHe spent practically all of his career in Portugal, recording over 270 games and 50 goals in the [[Primeira Liga]]. He represented four teams in the division, mainly [[C.D. Nacional|Nacional]] and [[Boavista F.C.|Boavista]].\n\nMateus made his debut for [[Angola national football team|Angola]] in 2006 and earned over 60 caps. He was selected for the [[2006 FIFA World Cup|2006 World Cup]] and four [[Africa Cup of Nations]] tournaments.\n\n==Club career==\nMateus was born in [[Luanda]]. After started playing professionally for modest [[Portugal|Portuguese]] teams (he had a stint with [[Sporting CP]], but never moved past [[Sporting CP B|their reserves]]), he signed in January 2006 with [[Gil Vicente F.C.]] of the [[Primeira Liga]]. He scored in his debut on 5 February, in a 5\u20130 home win against [[Vit\u00f3ria F.C.|Vit\u00f3ria de Set\u00fabal]].<ref>[http://www.record.xl.pt/arquivo/interior.aspx?content_id=260203 Gil Vicente-V. Set\u00fabal, 5\u20130: Grande treino do Gil (Gil Vicente-V. Set\u00fabal, 5\u20130: Great Gil training)]; [[Record (newspaper)|Record]], 6 February 2006 (in Portuguese)</ref>\n\nHowever, Mateus was at the centre of a judicial controversy that erupted in Portuguese football, known as ''Caso Mateus'' (Mateus Affair), after a supposedly illegal registration by the [[Barcelos, Portugal|Barcelos]] club. Following a lengthy judicial battle between Gil and [[C.F. Os Belenenses]], [[2005\u201306 Primeira Liga|the former were relegated]].<ref>[http://www.record.xl.pt/arquivo/interior.aspx?content_id=277046 \"Caso Mateus\": Gil Vicente pede explica\u00e7\u00f5es (\"Mateus Affair\": Gil Vicente ask for explanations)]; Record, 11 July 2006 (in Portuguese)</ref><ref>[http://www.uefa.com/news/newsid=447593.html Belenenses spared the drop]; UEFA, 22 August 2006</ref>\n\nAfter an uneventful [[2006\u201307 Liga de Honra|season]] with Gil Vicente in the [[Segunda Liga|second division]], greatly delayed by the legal consequences,<ref>[http://www.record.xl.pt/arquivo/interior.aspx?content_id=294044 Gil Vicente fica na Liga de Honra (Gil Vicente stay in Honour League)]; Record, 15 January 2007 (in Portuguese)</ref> Mateus joined [[Boavista F.C.]] for the [[2007\u201308 Primeira Liga|2007\u201308 campaign]]. His new team was also eventually relegated, due to irregularities.<ref>[http://www.uefa.com/memberassociations/news/newsid=693942.html Porto docked points, Boavista demoted]; UEFA, 9 May 2008</ref>\n\nIn [[2008\u201309 Primeira Liga|2008\u201309]], Mateus moved to [[Madeira]]'s [[C.D. Nacional]],<ref>[https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/nacional-mateus-assina-por-quatro-anos-com-acordo-do-boavista Nacional: Mateus assina por quatro anos com acordo do Boavista (Nacional: Mateus signs for four years after Boavista agree)]; Mais Futebol, 17 June 2008 (in Portuguese)</ref> being a regular in their attack as they [[2009\u201310 UEFA Europa League|qualified]] for the [[UEFA Europa League]]. In the same season, he played six games and scored four goals as they reached the semi-finals of the [[Ta\u00e7a de Portugal]], including one in each leg of a 5\u20132 aggregate elimination by [[F.C. Pa\u00e7os de Ferreira]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Pa\u00e7os de Ferreira na final da Ta\u00e7a de Portugal |url=https://www.rtp.pt/noticias/futebol-nacional/pacos-de-ferreira-na-final-da-taca-de-portugal_d262989 |accessdate=19 February 2020 |publisher=R\u00e1dio e Televis\u00e3o de Portugal|date=22 April 2009 |language=Portuguese}}</ref>\n\nMateus continued to be play frequently for the better part of the following years, notably netting nine goals in 24 matches in the [[2011\u201312 Primeira Liga|2011\u201312 season]]. On 7 April 2012, he netted twice in a 4\u20132 win at [[Funchal]] rivals [[C.S. Mar\u00edtimo]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Nacional goleia Mar\u00edtimo no d\u00e9rbi madeirense|trans-title=Nacional thrash Mar\u00edtimo in the Madeiran derby |url=https://www.rtp.pt/noticias/1a-liga/nacional-goleia-maritimo-no-derbi-madeirense_d543096 |accessdate=19 February 2020 |publisher=R\u00e1dio e Televis\u00e3o de Portugal |date=7 April 2012 |language=Portuguese}}</ref>\n\nOn 17 November 2013, Mateus moved to his country's league for the first time, signing for [[C.D. Primeiro de Agosto]] for the new year.<ref>{{cite news |title=Avan\u00e7ado do Nacional Mateus vai representar angolanos do 1\u00ba de Agosto|trans-title=Nacional striker Mateus will represent Angolans |url=https://www.rtp.pt/noticias/futebol-nacional/avancado-do-nacional-mateus-vai-representar-angolanos-do-1o-de-agosto_d696478 |accessdate=19 February 2020 |publisher=[[R\u00e1dio e Televis\u00e3o de Portugal]] |date=17 November 2013 |language=Portuguese}}</ref> In December 2015, he agreed a move back to Portugal's top flight, joining [[F.C. Arouca]] for the remainder of the season with the option of one more.<ref>{{cite news |title=Arouca: Mateus \u00e9 refor\u00e7o para o ataque a partir de janeiro|trans-title=Arouca: Mateus is addition for the attack starting from January |url=https://tvi24.iol.pt/liga/mercado/arouca-mateus-e-reforco-para-o-ataque-a-partir-de-janeiro |accessdate=19 February 2020 |publisher=[[TVI 24]] |date=20 December 2015 |language=Portuguese}}</ref>\n\nMateus returned to Boavista on 23 June 2017, signing a one-year deal a decade after first joining the club.<ref>{{cite news |title=Angolano Mateus est\u00e1 de volta ao Boavista |trans-title=Angolan Mateus back at Boavista|url=https://www.ojogo.pt/futebol/1a-liga/boavista/noticias/angolano-mateus-esta-de-volta-ao-boavista-8586083.html |accessdate=19 February 2020 |work=O Jogo |date=23 June 2017 |language=Portuguese}}</ref> After six goals in 31 games in his first season back at the ''[[Est\u00e1dio do Bessa]]'', he extended his link until 2020.<ref>{{cite news |title=Mateus renova com o Boavista at\u00e9 2020 |trans-title=Mateus renews with Boavista until 2020|url=https://desporto.sapo.ao/futebol/primeira-liga/artigos/mateus-renova-com-o-boavista-ate-2020 |accessdate=19 February 2020 |publisher=[[SAPO (company)|SAPO]] |date=16 May 2019 |language=Portuguese}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nAn [[Angola national football team|Angola international]] since 2006, Mateus was called up to [[2006 FIFA World Cup|that year]]'s [[FIFA World Cup]], playing in all three group stage matches including the entire 0\u20131 loss against [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]].<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/world_cup_2006/4852704.stm Angola 0\u20131 Portugal]; [[BBC Sport]], 11 June 2006</ref> He also added three substitute appearances in the [[2008 Africa Cup of Nations]], as the ''Palancas Negras'' reached the quarter-finals.\n\nOn 8 October 2011, Mateus scored as Angola won 2\u20130 away to [[Guinea-Bissau national football team|Guinea-Bissau]] to pip [[Uganda national football team|Uganda]] to a spot at the [[2012 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Magalh\u00e3es |first1=Anaximandro |title=Angola est\u00e1 no Campeonato Africano das Na\u00e7\u00f5es|trans-title=Angola is in the Africa Cup of Nations |url=http://jornaldeangola.sapo.ao/desporto/futebol/angola_esta_no_campeonato_africano_das_nacoes |accessdate=19 February 2020 |work=Jornal de Angola |date=9 October 2011 |language=Portuguese}}</ref> At the tournament in Gabon and Equatorial Guinea, he scored the first goal of their opening 2\u20131 win against [[Burkina Faso national football team|Burkina Faso]], but [[Lito Vidigal]]'s team were eliminated from the group.<ref>{{cite news |title=Angola seal victory over Burkina Faso |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/sport/football/2012/01/201212221342669351.html |accessdate=19 February 2020 |publisher=[[Al Jazeera]] |date=22 January 2012}}</ref> A year later, he started all three games as the team exited at the same stage.\n\nMateus scored four times in [[2019 Africa Cup of Nations qualification|qualification]] for the [[2019 Africa Cup of Nations]], coming in braces in wins over [[Mauritania national football team|Mauritania]] (4\u20131) and Burkina Faso (2\u20131).<ref>{{cite news |title=CAN\u20192019: Angola esmagou a Maurit\u00e2nia|trans-title=ACN'2019: Angola crushed Mauritania |url=http://www.rfi.fr/pt/angola/20181012-can-2019-angola-esmagou-mauritania-futebol-palancas-negras-angolanos |accessdate=19 February 2020 |publisher=RFI |date=12 October 2018 |language=Portuguese}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Angola beats Burkina Faso and rejoins the race for the Cup |url=https://www.plataformamedia.com/en-uk/sport/football/angola-beats-burkina-faso-and-rejoins-the-race-for-the-cup--10196714.html |accessdate=19 February 2020 |date=19 November 2018}}</ref> He [[Captain (association football)|captained]] the side at the finals in Egypt, falling again at the first hurdle.<ref>{{cite news |title=CAN 2019: Mateus, capit\u00e3o dos Palancas Negras abriu o cora\u00e7\u00e3o|trans-title=ACN 2019: Mateus, captain of the ''Palancas Negras'' opened his heart |url=http://www.rfi.fr/pt/angola/20190705-can-2019-mateus-capitao-dos-palancas-negras-abriu-o-coracao-angola-futebol |accessdate=19 February 2020 |publisher=RFI |date=5 July 2019 |language=Portuguese}}</ref>\n\n===International goals===\n{{updated|12 October 2018}} (Angola score listed first, score column indicates score after each Mateus goal)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/mateus-galiano-da-costa/98/matches/|title=Mateus \u2013 Matches|publisher=Soccerway|accessdate=12 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/ango-mateus-intl.html|title=Mateus Galiano da Costa \u2013 International Appearances|publisher=[[Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation|RSSSF]]|accessdate=10 March 2017}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=font-size:95%\n!#\n!Date\n!Venue\n!Opponent\n!Score\n!Result\n!Competition\n|-\n|1.\n|29 April 2006\n|[[Setsoto Stadium]], [[Maseru]], [[Lesotho]]\n|{{fb|Mauritius}}\n|<center>4\u20131</center>\n|<center>5\u20131</center>\n|rowspan=2|[[2006 COSAFA Cup]]\n|-\n|2.\n|30 April 2006\n|Setsoto Stadium, Maseru, Lesotho\n|{{fb|Lesotho|1987}}\n|<center>1\u20130</center>\n|<center>3\u20131</center>\n|-\n|3.\n|8 October 2006\n|[[Est\u00e1dio da Cidadela]], [[Luanda]], [[Angola]]\n|{{fb|Kenya}}\n|<center>2\u20130</center>\n|<center>3\u20131</center>\n|[[2008 Africa Cup of Nations qualification#Qualifying round#Group 6|2008 Africa Cup of Nations qualification]]\n|-\n|4.\n|12 August 2009\n|[[Est\u00e1dio do Restelo]], [[Lisbon]], [[Portugal]]\n|{{fb|Togo}}\n|<center>2\u20130</center>\n|<center>2\u20130</center>\n|[[Exhibition game|Friendly]]\n|-\n|5.\n|8 October 2011\n|[[Est\u0